#: ../../source/configure/bleve-search.rst:7
msgid ""
"Bleve is a search engine that uses Lucene-style full-text search and "
"indexing. This style of search and indexing helps overcome limitations of"
" the default database search such as challenges with characters and "
"advanced search capabilities."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configure/bleve-search.rst:9
msgid ""
"The Bleve search engine works as a library integrated into the Mattermost"
" codebase. As it generates indexes in the filesystem of the server that "
"it is running on, it doesnâ€™t require an external server to function. "
"Because of this, Bleve should not be enabled in High Availability "
"deployments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configure/bleve-search.rst:13
msgid ""
"Bleve search uses the scorch index type on newly-created indexes. This "
"new index type features efficiency improvements and indexes that use "
"significantly less disk space. Go to **System Console > Experimental > "
"Bleve** and select **Purge Index** to run a purge operation. When that's "
"complete, select **Index Now** to reindex. Bleve remains compatible with "
"existing indexes, so currently indexed data will continue to work if a "
"purge and reindex isn't run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configure/bleve-search.rst:16
msgid "Configuring Bleve in Mattermost"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configure/bleve-search.rst:18
msgid ""
"Follow these steps to configure the Mattermost server to use Bleve and "
"generate required indexes. Once the configuration is saved, new posts "
"made to the database will be automatically indexed with Bleve."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configure/bleve-search.rst:20
msgid ""
"**Note:** During indexing, search results may be incomplete until the "
"indexing job is complete."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configure/bleve-search.rst:22
msgid "Open **System Console > Experimental > Bleve**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configure/bleve-search.rst:23
msgid ""
"Set **Enable Bleve Indexing** to **true** to enable the other settings on"
" the page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configure/bleve-search.rst:24
msgid ""
"Set the directory path to use for storing Bleve indexes (e.g.: "
"``/var/opt/mattermost/bleveindexes``). The user running Mattermost should"
" have permissions to access the directory. See our :ref:`configuration "
"settings <configure/experimental-configuration-settings:experimental "
"bleve configuration settings>`  documentation for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configure/bleve-search.rst:25
msgid "Save the configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configure/bleve-search.rst:26
msgid ""
"Select **Index Now**. All users, channels, and posts in the database will"
" be indexed oldest to newest."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configure/bleve-search.rst:27
msgid "Set **Enable Bleve for search queries** to **true**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configure/bleve-search.rst:28
msgid "Set **Enable Bleve for autocomplete queries** to **true**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configure/bleve-search.rst:32
msgid ""
"Search results for files shared before upgrading to Mattermost Server "
"v5.35 may be incomplete until an extraction command is run using the "
":ref:`mmctl <manage/mmctl-command-line-tool:mmctl extract>`. After "
"running this command, the search index must be rebuilt. Go to **System "
"Console > Experimental > Bleve > Bulk Indexing**, then select **Index "
"Now** to rebuild the search index to include older file contents."
msgstr ""

